cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.NA 

This paper deals with diffusion processes, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses graph clustering, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of diffusion processes in applied mathematics suggests cs.SD (Systems and Control) as another possible category. Finally, the paper introduces a novel algorithm, which involves optimization, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a plausible category as well.
